Feature: Killing lines

  Scenario: Killing a comment
    When I insert:
    """
    //function foo() {
    //    bar();
    //}
    """
    And I turn on js2-mode
    And I go to the front of the word "function"
    And I press "C-c C-m k"
    Then I should see:
    """
    //
    //    bar();
    //}
    """

  Scenario: Killing a with parse errors
    When I insert:
    """
    function foo(
        bar();
    }
    """
    And I turn on js2-mode
    And I go to the front of the word "function"
    And I press "C-c C-m k"
    Then I should see:
    """
    
        bar();
    }
    """


  Scenario: Killing in a string
    When I insert:
    """
    function foo() {
        bar('hello world');
    }
    """
    And I turn on js2-mode
    And I go to the front of the word "world"
    And I press "C-c C-m k"
    Then I should see:
    """
    function foo() {
        bar('hello ');
    }
    """
